#MEM id=ice-scoring-framework source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/nate/skills/custom/ice-scoring-framework/SKILL.md
M|ice-scoring-framework|name: ice-scoring-framework
M|ice-scoring-framework|description: YVON-calibrated ICE scoring for growth experiment prioritisation. Defines Impact, Confidence, and Effort scales anchored to Novizio and Hourbour's business models. Load before scoring any
M|ice-scoring-framework|version: 1.0.0
M|ice-scoring-framework|ICE scoring without calibration is noise. "Impact 9" on a Novizio experiment means something specific — it moves purchase conversion. "Impact 9" on a Hourbour experiment means something different — it
M|ice-scoring-framework|```
M|ice-scoring-framework|ICE = (Impact + Confidence + Effort) / 3
M|ice-scoring-framework|```
M|ice-scoring-framework|Each dimension scored 1–10. Effort is inverse: 10 = lowest effort (easiest to run).
M|ice-scoring-framework|**Priority thresholds:**
M|ice-scoring-framework|| ICE Score | Action |
M|ice-scoring-framework||-----------|--------|
M|ice-scoring-framework|| ≥ 7.0 | Fast track — run in current sprint |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 5.0–6.9 | Queue — schedule in next sprint |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 3.0–4.9 | Backlog — revisit when higher-scored experiments are done |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| < 3.0 | Drop — effort exceeds expected return |
M|ice-scoring-framework|**Novizio (Fashion E-commerce) — Impact anchors:**
M|ice-scoring-framework|| Score | What it moves |
M|ice-scoring-framework||-------|--------------|
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 9–10 | Directly increases purchase conversion rate or average order value |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 7–8 | Increases add-to-cart rate or reduces cart abandonment |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 5–6 | Increases product page engagement (time on page, scroll depth) |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 3–4 | Increases site traffic or soc engagement without direct conversion path |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 1–2 | Brand awareness only — no measurable conversion signal within 14 days |
M|ice-scoring-framework|**Hourbour (SaaS Subscription) — Impact anchors:**
M|ice-scoring-framework|| Score | What it moves |
M|ice-scoring-framework||-------|--------------|
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 9–10 | Directly increases trial-to-paid conversion or reduces monthly churn |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 7–8 | Increases activation rate (users reaching first key action within 7 days) |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 5–6 | Increases trial signups from landing page |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 3–4 | Increases traffic, leads, or trial starts without activation data |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 1–2 | Brand awareness only — no measurable subscription signal within 14 days |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| Score | Evidence basis |
M|ice-scoring-framework||-------|---------------|
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 9–10 | 3+ comparable experiments with consistent results (own data) |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 7–8 | 1–2 comparable experiments or strong analogous data from similar businesses |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 5–6 | Qualitative evidence: user interviews, surveys, or ses recordings — no direct conversion data |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 3–4 | Logical inference from related data (e.g., industry benchmarks, Kai's trend data) |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 1–2 | Pure hypothesis — no supporting evidence beyond intuition |
M|ice-scoring-framework|**Rule:** Never round up Confidence. If evidence is thin, score it thin. A wrong high-Confidence score burns 14 days on a bad bet.
M|ice-scoring-framework|| Score | Effort required |
M|ice-scoring-framework||-------|----------------|
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 9–10 | < 1 day to implement, Nate or Lena/Rio executes without Dev/Raj |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 7–8 | 1–3 days, single DRI can execute (no tec dependency) |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 5–6 | 3–7 days, requires one Dev/Raj resource |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 3–4 | 1–2 weeks, cross-team coordination required |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 1–2 | > 2 weeks or major engineering lift |
M|ice-scoring-framework|**Common underestimation patterns:**
M|ice-scoring-framework|- "It's just a quick copy change" → check with Lena: how long does a complete variant take?
M|ice-scoring-framework|- "It's just a design tweak" → check with Mia: what's the actual implementation time?
M|ice-scoring-framework|- "It's already built" → check with Dev/Raj: is it actually deployable in current state?
M|ice-scoring-framework|For every experiment, state scores AND assumptions:
M|ice-scoring-framework|```
M|ice-scoring-framework|Experiment: [name]
M|ice-scoring-framework|Impact: [score] — assumes [specific outcome and which funnel stage]
M|ice-scoring-framework|Confidence: [score] — based on [specific evidence or data source]
M|ice-scoring-framework|Effort: [score] — assumes [who executes, estimated time, dependencies]
M|ice-scoring-framework|ICE: [calculated average]
M|ice-scoring-framework|```
M|ice-scoring-framework|**Example:**
M|ice-scoring-framework|```
M|ice-scoring-framework|Experiment: Add size guide popup to Novizio PDP
M|ice-scoring-framework|Impact: 7 — assumes reducing size uncertainty increases ATC rate by 10–15%
M|ice-scoring-framework|Confidence: 5 — based on 2 user interviews citing sizing as a hesitation; no split test data
M|ice-scoring-framework|Effort: 8 — Mia estimated 2 days for design + implementation
M|ice-scoring-framework|ICE: 6.7 → Queue
M|ice-scoring-framework|```
M|ice-scoring-framework|After every experiment resolves, compare predicted vs actual impact:
M|ice-scoring-framework|| If predicted Impact was... | And actual was... | Update |
M|ice-scoring-framework||---------------------------|------------------|--------|
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 8, actual 3 | Overestimated | Reduce confidence on similar hypotheses by 1–2 points |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| 5, actual 8 | Underestimated | Increase priority of similar experiments; refine anchor definitions |
M|ice-scoring-framework|| Consistent with prediction | Well-calibrated | No change needed |
M|ice-scoring-framework|A scoring model that consistently over- or under-predicts is the problem — not the experiments.